Privacy Policy for Aitor
Effective Date: July 4, 2024
1. Introduction
Welcome to Aitor (the "Bot"). We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of any personal data we collect. This Privacy Policy outlines the types of information we collect from users of our Bot, how we use that information, and the steps we take to safeguard it.

2. Information We Collect
2.1 User Data: When you interact with Aitor, we may collect certain information such as your Discord user ID, username, and any messages or commands you send to the Bot.

2.2 Usage Data: We may also collect information on how the Bot is accessed and used. This includes data such as the time and date of your interactions, the features used, and other diagnostic data.

3. How We Use Your Information
3.1 To Provide and Maintain the Bot: We use the information collected to operate and maintain the Bot, ensure its functionality, and provide you with support.

3.2 To Improve the Bot: We may use your data to analyze usage patterns and improve the Botâ€™s performance and features.

3.3 Communication: If necessary, we may use your information to contact you with updates, security alerts, or support messages related to the Bot.

4. Data Security
We are committed to ensuring the security of your data. We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction.

5. Data Sharing and Disclosure
We do not share or sell your personal information to third parties. However, we may disclose your information if required to do so by law or in response to valid requests by public authorities (e.g., a court or a government agency).

6. Data Retention
We will retain your personal data only for as long as is necessary for the purposes set out in this Privacy Policy. We will also retain and use your information to the extent necessary to comply with our legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our policies.

7. Your Rights
Depending on your location, you may have the following rights regarding your personal data:

The right to access and obtain a copy of your data.
The right to rectify any inaccurate or incomplete data.
The right to erase your data, under certain conditions.
The right to restrict or object to the processing of your data, under certain conditions.
8. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the effective date. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.

9. Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at [Your Contact Information].

By using Aitor, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
